    "substrate-desc": {
      "type": "text",
      "variant": "prose",
      "props": {
        "content": "Lev's strongest subsystems converge on: **declaration → compiler → IR → runtime → federation**. This is not metaphorical — each layer has a concrete implementation:\n\n**Declaration** = config.yaml, .flow.yaml, dna/*.yaml (the authored truth)\n**Compiler** = lev install / config resolver (normalize, validate, lower)\n**IR** = entity graph + event store (stable form, 944 entities, multiple consumers)\n**Runtime** = graph-os.ai / local Lev / ClawBuddy / kingly.cloud (projections)\n**Federation** = graph.store mesh (5th substrate layer — discovery, composition, credit settlement)"
      }
    },
